==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: chorale
<hw>chorale</hw></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A stately hymn tune; a simple sacred tune, sung
in unison by the congregation, used mostly in Protestant (especially
Lutheran) churches; <as>as, the Lutheran <ex>chorals</ex></as>.</def>
<altsp>[Sometimes written <asp>chorale</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Choralist</ent>⟦br⟧
